{"id":489,"category_slug":"english-conversations","category_name":"Conversations","position":90,"title":"90. Applying for a job","subtitle":"","level":"B1","parts":25,"url":"https://dailydictation.com/exercises/english-conversations/90-applying-for-a-job.489/listen-and-type","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/90-applying-for-a-job-2022-03-07-21-35-19/0-90-applying-for-a-job.mp3","transcript":"Come in... come in. It's Miss Wallace, isn't it?\nYes, that's right. How do you do?\nHow do you do? Please take a seat.\nThank you very much.\nWell, I've got your application form here.\nI just want to check the information... is that all right?\nYes, of course.\nNow, you're 28, aren't you?\nYes, I am.\nAnd you aren't married, are you?\nNo, I'm not... yet; I'm engaged.\nUh, huh. You didn't go to university?\nNo, I didn't, but I went to technical college.\nAnd I started work when I was 20.\nI see. You can speak Spanish, can't you?\nYes, I can... but I can write it better than I can speak it.\nIs there any other language you can speak?\nYes, I can speak a little French.\nYou've been to Argentina, haven't you?\nYes, I have... and to France.\nSo I see... but you haven't been to the Middle East, have you?\nNo, I'm afraid I haven't, but I'd like to.\nGood, because there is a demand for multi-lingual people in this job.\nI think you will do just fine!\nThank you so much! I won't disappoint you!","youtube_video_id":"","details_cached_at":"2026-06-15T20:49:08","challenges":[{"position":1,"content":"Come in... come in. It's Miss Wallace, isn't it?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/90-applying-for-a-job-2022-03-07-21-35-19/1.mp3","time_start":2.47,"time_end":5.0},{"position":2,"content":"Yes, that's right. How do you do?","audio_url":"https://dailydictation.com/upload/english-conversations/90-applying-for-a-job-2022-03-07-21-35-19/2.mp3","time_start":5.0,"time_end":7.02},{"position":3,"content":"How do you do? Please ta